@vitovtnet is it allowed to pass `Expression` as `operand1` in operator format condition?
And it's not clear what you want to achieve using this.
As you said `$this->andFilterWhere(['<=', operation_date , $openingDate->format('Y-m-d')]);` works correct and it is correct condition.

Also, I checked all mo code which written 05.04.2018 (more than a year ago), I'm everywhere used a construction like

```
 if (!empty($this->endDate)) {
            $endDate = new \DateTime($this->endDate);

            $query->andFilterWhere([
                '<=',
                new Expression('operation_booking_date'),
                $endDate->format('Y-m-d') ]);
        }
```
And it's worked

Same problem in LikeConditionBuilder, InConditionBuilder.

I redefined yii\db\Connection::quoteColumnName() method in my project. Maybe, is it a bad idea?

```php
public function quoteColumnName($name)
{
   if ($name instanceof ExpressionInterface) {
        return (string)$name;
   }

   return parent::quoteColumnName($name);
}
```

